===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|morter}}, from {{der|en|fro|mortier}}, from {{der|en|la|mortārium}}. {{doublet|en|mortarium}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˈmɔːtə(ɹ)/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-mortar.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɔː(ɹ)tə(ɹ)|s=2}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A mixture of [[lime]] or [[cement]], [[sand]] and [[water]] used for [[bonding]] [[building block]]s.
# {{lb|en|countable}} A muzzle-loading, [[indirect]] fire [[weapon]] with a tube length of 10 to 20 [[caliber]]s and designed to lob [[shell]]s at very steep [[trajectories]].
# {{lb|en|countable}} A hollow [[vessel]] used to [[pound]], [[crush]], [[rub]], [[grind]] or [[mix]] [[ingredient]]s with a [[pestle]].
# {{lb|en|countable}} In paper milling, a [[trough]] in which material is [[hammer]]ed.

